    "summary": "Chris is a video artist & designer, visual researcher, journalist and knowmad. He was born in Santiago, Chile, studied and worked both in Chile and The Netherlands, and is now based in Melbourne, Australia. He completed a bachelor\u00b4s degree in Journalism and Social Communication (2001), a Master of Arts (2007) and a Master of Philosophy (2013).\n  \nHe fosters a unique approach to creative work that combines a handcrafted use of digital visual technology and a fascination for meaningful collaboration with global cultures at a local scale. He is passionate about exploring nomadic and sustainable ways of creative work, exchange and horizontal learning through the development of projects, techniques and experiences for creative fair trade. \n\nAlong 12 years of professional work, he has gathered experience in the visual design of a wide range of creative fields including contemporary dance, theatre, photography and light performance. Today, his fascination for exploring the world combined with his passion for video making, has crystallized in the project ''Motion Postcards'', a grassroots familiar partnership involving wanderlust, meaningful interaction with local communities and the development of high quality audiovisual products for the upcoming Internet.\n\nSpecialties: Video design, visual media research, concept design, art direction, live performance, audiovisual production.",
